Speaking with @JudgeJeanine on Fox News in just a few minutes.

Like many members of the House & Senate, I’ve been on the phone all day trying to get people out of Afghanistan.

The Taliban are playing games, slow-walking evacuations, & clearly setting up a hostage situation post-August 31. 

The Biden Administration needs to up their game.
Joining @seanhannity shortly on @FoxNews — tune in.

Any sustainable solution in Afghanistan must include Pakistan. 
 
We all must remember Pakistan is a nuclear-armed nation, and there is a Pakistan version of the Taliban who wishes topple the Pakistani government and military. 
 
Very complicated region and dangerous times.

Just spoke with the Ambassador of Pakistan to the United States about the situation in Afghanistan. 
 
Very much appreciate the efforts of the Pakistani government to assist with the evacuation of U.S. citizens, our allies, and other nations.

My condolences go to their families and my deep appreciation for the ultimate sacrifice they gave to their country in an honorable operation to rescue their fellow citizens trapped behind enemy lines.

May they Rest in Peace.
Very sad to hear that in our efforts to evacuate American citizens and Afghan allies we have lost 13 U.S. service members.
The retaking of Bagram would put our military at risk, but I think those involved in the operation would gladly accept that risk because it would restore our honor as a nation and save lives.

I urge the Biden Administration to reestablish our presence in Bagram as an alternative to the Kabul airport so that we do not leave our fellow citizens and thousands of Afghan allies behind.

It is not a capability problem, but a problem of will.

We have the capability to reestablish our presence at Bagram to continue to evacuate American citizens and our Afghan allies.
 
The biggest mistake in this debacle is abandoning Bagram.
I have advocated for days that the Bagram Air Base should be reopened as the Kabul airport is very difficult to defend and has been the only evacuation outlet.
This despicable terrorist attack against innocent civilians at the Kabul airport, which injured American Marines, is a reminder of the depravity the world faces from Afghanistan.

My friend @HerschelWalker just announced his candidacy for the United States Senate in Georgia! 

Please join me in supporting his campaign from Day One! https://t.co/O29xmJpQLi

My thoughts today are with the McCain clan.  
 
RIP my friend.

In many ways, I’m glad he’s not here to see the debacle in Afghanistan because it would have truly broken his heart.  
 
John was passionate about national security and driven by a sense of duty and honor that I believe represent the best of America.
On this, the third anniversary of John McCain’s passing - and given the chaos in the world - it reminds me and many others how much we miss his counsel and wisdom.
Unfortunately, when it comes to Afghanistan and other national security problems, the worst is yet to come.
The fault lies with President Biden, who doesn’t have the critical thinking skills to make adjustments and has always been more political with foreign policy than conditions-based.

In the Afghanistan withdrawal:

He put in motion the leaving behind of thousands of Afghans who fought by our side, American citizens, and billions of dollars worth of American military hardware.

In the case of President Biden:

He consistently rejects sound military advice and substitutes his own judgement - which over the arc of time - has been a disaster.

Speaking with @seanhannity on Fox News in just a few minutes about Afghanistan.

I cannot believe the Commander-in-Chief would address the nation today and NOT discuss Afghanistan.
President Biden and his team are derelict in their duty to protect American citizens and our Afghan allies who are at the mercy of the Taliban.
I cannot believe the Commander-in-Chief would address the nation today and NOT discuss Afghanistan.

When it comes to evacuating American citizens and our Afghan allies who fought bravely by our side, there should not be a clock nor a question of capability.
 
We have the capability and there should be no time limit – the only question is, do we have the will?
Just can’t believe I heard the Secretary of Defense say that we will get American citizens and our Afghan allies out of Afghanistan until the clock runs out or we run out of capability.
The best thing that can happen for Afghan women is if those in charge of this debacle at the State Department resign and be replaced by more competent individuals.
The audacity to talk about how much she cares for Afghan women – in light of the actions of the Biden Administration – is beyond shameless.

The Biden Administration has abandoned Afghan women! 

The fate that awaits Afghan women, at the hands of the Taliban, is a direct result of the Biden Administration’s failure to adequately plan for an ill-conceived withdrawal.

I can’t believe what I heard from the State Department briefing podium by Deputy Secretary of State Wendy Sherman.

She went through all of her efforts to improve the lives of Afghan women going back to 1997 and now believes that those words matter.

Speaking with @SandraSmithFox today at 1:00 pm about the situation in Afghanistan.

Tune in!

It is only a matter of time until al-Qaeda reemerges in Afghanistan and presents a threat to the American homeland and western world.  

President Biden seems oblivious to the terrorist threats that will come from a Taliban-run Afghanistan.
It is only a matter of time until al-Qaeda reforms in Afghanistan and presents a threat to the American homeland and western world.

The takeover of Afghanistan by the Taliban is a sad and dangerous event for U.S. national security interests and the world at large.  

Jihadists all over the world are celebrating this event.

The military is doing the best they can given the bad hand they have been dealt.  

The people wearing the suits created this debacle - not the ones wearing the uniform.

Our military leaders can only advise.  

It is up to the political leadership – the Commander-in-Chief and his team – to act.  

The decision to withdraw completely from Afghanistan was made AGAINST sound military advice.
Our military leaders understand the benefit of a residual force to protect Afghanistan from becoming a failed state and also to prevent the rise of al-Qaeda and ISIS.
